1
00:00:00,767 --> 00:00:04,100
[DRAMATIC TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

2
00:00:04,233 --> 00:00:06,233
We're being feasted on
by the news.

3
00:00:06,367 --> 00:00:09,100
The entire business community
is laughing at us.

4
00:00:09,233 --> 00:00:10,733
That's your problem!

5
00:00:10,867 --> 00:00:12,300
All of us have to follow you

6
00:00:12,433 --> 00:00:14,500
because if we don't,
you throw us away like trash!

7
00:00:14,633 --> 00:00:15,833
Marjorie, be quiet!

8
00:00:15,967 --> 00:00:17,267
I will not be quiet, Dad!

9
00:00:17,400 --> 00:00:18,700
Just a little more effort,

10
00:00:18,833 --> 00:00:22,033
and you'll get back everything
you deserve in this house.

11
00:00:22,167 --> 00:00:24,133
- Dad!
- Your mistress' husband

12
00:00:24,267 --> 00:00:25,500
had a heart attack.

13
00:00:25,633 --> 00:00:28,933
The Torrecampos are slowly
self destructing.

14
00:00:29,067 --> 00:00:30,233
That's your karma.

15
00:00:30,367 --> 00:00:32,433
And this is also the way for all
the suffering you caused us

16
00:00:32,567 --> 00:00:33,667
to finally end!

17
00:00:34,800 --> 00:00:38,300
[DRAMATIC TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

18
00:00:53,767 --> 00:00:57,300
[DRAMATIC TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

19
00:01:04,867 --> 00:01:10,000
[DRAMATIC TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

20
00:01:17,900 --> 00:01:20,500
Let me explain.

21
00:01:20,633 --> 00:01:22,733
- Mom!
- [CLAMORING]

22
00:01:22,867 --> 00:01:24,300
- Stop it!
- Dad, stop it!

23
00:01:24,433 --> 00:01:26,133
You're going to kill mom!

24
00:01:26,267 --> 00:01:27,767
Don't interfere!

25
00:01:27,900 --> 00:01:29,567
This is that woman's fault!

26
00:01:29,700 --> 00:01:31,333
She destroyed this family!

27
00:01:31,467 --> 00:01:32,700
She destroyed me!

28
00:01:32,833 --> 00:01:34,533
She ruined me!

29
00:01:37,267 --> 00:01:39,367
That woman screwed me over!

30
00:01:39,500 --> 00:01:41,800
I'll make her pay
for making me a fool!

31
00:01:41,967 --> 00:01:45,333
- Dad, Dad!
- Dad, stop it! Please stop!

32
00:01:45,467 --> 00:01:48,933
You have the nerve
to raise your voice at me!

33
00:01:49,067 --> 00:01:50,667
That's your problem!

34
00:01:50,800 --> 00:01:53,133
All of us are afraid of you!

35
00:01:53,267 --> 00:01:55,133
We all have to obey you
because if we don't,

36
00:01:55,267 --> 00:01:57,700
you throw us away like trash!

37
00:01:57,833 --> 00:02:00,633
Nobody calls you out
even when you're already wrong!

38
00:02:00,767 --> 00:02:02,967
Don't turn the blame on me!

39
00:02:04,333 --> 00:02:05,900
That woman deceived us!

40
00:02:06,033 --> 00:02:07,200
She's the one who lied!

41
00:02:07,333 --> 00:02:11,367
I became cruel to my own child
because of her!

42
00:02:11,500 --> 00:02:14,200
Yes, mom has faults.

43
00:02:14,367 --> 00:02:16,167
But if there's someone
who should be blamed here,

44
00:02:16,300 --> 00:02:17,767
it's you!

45
00:02:17,900 --> 00:02:19,700
If only you had been faithful
as a spouse,

46
00:02:19,833 --> 00:02:21,700
mom wouldn't have cheated.

47
00:02:21,833 --> 00:02:24,300
If you had been a good
and faithful parent,

48
00:02:24,433 --> 00:02:26,667
Edward wouldn't have
grown distant from you!

49
00:02:26,800 --> 00:02:28,133
Marjorie, be quiet!

50
00:02:28,267 --> 00:02:30,433
I will not be quiet, Dad!

51
00:02:30,567 --> 00:02:32,800
We all loved you!

52
00:02:32,933 --> 00:02:35,900
Edward and mom gave
their whole lives to you

53
00:02:36,033 --> 00:02:39,267
just to please you,
but you ignored them!

54
00:02:39,400 --> 00:02:41,033
You ruined their lives!

55
00:02:41,167 --> 00:02:43,533
You destroyed all of our lives!

56
00:02:45,033 --> 00:02:46,433
Mom, come on.

57
00:02:46,567 --> 00:02:50,167
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

58
00:03:11,833 --> 00:03:15,133
Dad, I don't know
how to begin this.

59
00:03:16,467 --> 00:03:17,967
I just want to say...

60
00:03:20,400 --> 00:03:21,467
I'm sorry.

61
00:03:24,267 --> 00:03:28,100
Not because I'm guilty,
but because...

62
00:03:29,500 --> 00:03:32,067
I disappointed you.

63
00:03:32,200 --> 00:03:34,833
Because I'm not really
your child.

64
00:03:34,967 --> 00:03:36,800
But more than that,

65
00:03:36,933 --> 00:03:38,900
Dad, thank you for everything.

66
00:03:40,667 --> 00:03:43,400
Thank you for everything
you gave me.

67
00:03:45,400 --> 00:03:48,300
Thank you for everything
you taught me.

68
00:03:49,367 --> 00:03:51,733
You taught me how to be
a leader,

69
00:03:51,867 --> 00:03:53,700
how to be strong...

70
00:03:54,800 --> 00:03:59,267
how to carry the Torrecampo name
with pride.

71
00:04:02,700 --> 00:04:04,467
I know I'm not your blood...

72
00:04:05,833 --> 00:04:08,433
and you're not my real father,

73
00:04:13,867 --> 00:04:15,733
but I want you to know that...

74
00:04:19,700 --> 00:04:24,867
you're the only one
I will acknowledge

75
00:04:25,000 --> 00:04:27,200
and consider my father.

76
00:04:29,600 --> 00:04:36,600
Because for me,
you are my only dad.

77
00:04:38,633 --> 00:04:41,367
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

78
00:04:41,500 --> 00:04:43,000
[SOBS]

79
00:04:46,600 --> 00:04:54,000
["KATOTOHANAN" THEME MUSIC
PLAYING]

80
00:04:56,900 --> 00:04:58,533
[GLASS SHATTERS]

81
00:05:16,033 --> 00:05:17,000
Look at this.

82
00:05:19,267 --> 00:05:22,333
We're being feasted on
by the news.

83
00:05:22,467 --> 00:05:25,633
We're being laughed at by the
entire business community.

84
00:05:27,033 --> 00:05:29,967
This family is completely
destroyed.

85
00:05:30,100 --> 00:05:34,300
Dad, please don't blame us
for everything.

86
00:05:34,467 --> 00:05:35,767
No, Marj.

87
00:05:37,933 --> 00:05:39,733
I'm not blaming you.

88
00:05:40,900 --> 00:05:44,367
I thought all night
about what you said

89
00:05:44,500 --> 00:05:47,367
and I realized you're right.

90
00:05:48,500 --> 00:05:50,033
It's all my fault.

91
00:05:52,600 --> 00:05:54,333
My pride,

92
00:05:54,467 --> 00:05:55,700
my blindness...

93
00:05:57,033 --> 00:05:59,567
I brought us to this situation.

94
00:06:02,800 --> 00:06:04,800
Edward, my son...

95
00:06:07,800 --> 00:06:09,133
I'm sorry.

96
00:06:11,133 --> 00:06:17,033
Sorry for the way I treated you
all these years.

97
00:06:20,367 --> 00:06:22,033
Forgive me...

98
00:06:24,967 --> 00:06:27,533
because I let my anger
outweigh my trust

99
00:06:29,833 --> 00:06:31,833
in my own blood.

100
00:06:34,967 --> 00:06:36,267
I'm sorry.

101
00:06:40,533 --> 00:06:41,967
That's it?

102
00:06:42,667 --> 00:06:43,800
Just sorry?

103
00:06:45,000 --> 00:06:46,700
Dad, it's not enough!

104
00:06:47,400 --> 00:06:50,600
If you really want to prove
you want to make things right,

105
00:06:50,733 --> 00:06:52,200
prove it.

106
00:06:54,533 --> 00:06:56,767
Let's start
by cleaning this house.

107
00:06:58,367 --> 00:06:59,767
Kick these two out

108
00:06:59,900 --> 00:07:01,900
because they don't deserve
to stay here.

109
00:07:02,633 --> 00:07:03,733
Thea, what are you doing?

110
00:07:03,867 --> 00:07:06,233
We're trying to fix the family.

111
00:07:06,367 --> 00:07:10,667
We're saving what's left of us,
and you want to kick us out?

112
00:07:10,800 --> 00:07:14,400
Marj, we are the only family
here.

113
00:07:15,033 --> 00:07:17,633
Get that into your thick head!

114
00:07:17,767 --> 00:07:21,733
Only Edward truly
has Torrecampo blood.

115
00:07:21,867 --> 00:07:25,833
Your spouse
is just illegitimate,

116
00:07:25,967 --> 00:07:27,133
so he has no right!

117
00:07:27,267 --> 00:07:28,367
Thea!

118
00:07:29,567 --> 00:07:32,133
Paolo is still a legal
Torrecampo.

119
00:07:32,267 --> 00:07:36,000
He carries that name
because Greg acknowledged him.

120
00:07:37,067 --> 00:07:41,900
And let me remind you,
I am still the wife of Greg.

121
00:07:42,033 --> 00:07:44,933
So I have a say
who stays in this house

122
00:07:45,067 --> 00:07:47,267
because this is
conjugal property.

123
00:07:49,000 --> 00:07:55,300
So, I still own this mansion
you're standing in.

124
00:07:55,433 --> 00:07:57,233
Wow!

125
00:07:57,367 --> 00:08:00,533
And who started all this chaos?

126
00:08:01,600 --> 00:08:04,567
Watch how you speak to mom,
don't be rude.

127
00:08:04,700 --> 00:08:07,000
Is that your strategy now, Marj?

128
00:08:07,133 --> 00:08:10,967
Sucking up to mom
because you know dad hates you?

129
00:08:11,100 --> 00:08:12,600
Stop it, Thea.

130
00:08:12,733 --> 00:08:14,067
Don't start trouble.

131
00:08:14,200 --> 00:08:15,900
Why should I stop?

132
00:08:16,033 --> 00:08:20,400
If we don't assert our rights,
they'll walk all over us again!

133
00:08:20,533 --> 00:08:22,367
They'll treat us
like trash again!

134
00:08:22,533 --> 00:08:24,833
No way! Never again!

135
00:08:24,967 --> 00:08:26,467
If you don't want to be treated
like trash,

136
00:08:26,600 --> 00:08:28,200
then don't act like trash.

137
00:08:28,333 --> 00:08:30,433
And don't act like a saint!

138
00:08:30,567 --> 00:08:31,800
Because if you were truly good,

139
00:08:31,933 --> 00:08:35,367
you wouldn't steal what should
go to my spouse and to us.

140
00:08:35,500 --> 00:08:38,633
Wait a second! Who's really
greedy between the two of us?

141
00:08:41,567 --> 00:08:43,500
Marj, please. Don't engage.

142
00:08:43,633 --> 00:08:45,133
I told you to stop.

143
00:08:45,267 --> 00:08:47,100
Why are you defending them?

144
00:08:47,233 --> 00:08:48,700
They stole your life.

145
00:08:48,833 --> 00:08:50,533
They're the reason
we're at a disadvantage!

146
00:08:50,667 --> 00:08:52,567
Step aside,
I'll lecture this woman!

147
00:08:52,700 --> 00:08:53,633
- [CLAMORING]
- You're the one who started

148
00:08:53,767 --> 00:08:55,300
all this chaos!

149
00:08:56,167 --> 00:08:57,633
Flirt! Flirt!

150
00:08:57,767 --> 00:08:58,700
You're trash!

151
00:08:58,833 --> 00:09:01,200
[CLAMORING]

152
00:09:01,333 --> 00:09:02,667
You have no right!

153
00:09:06,900 --> 00:09:07,933
Dad?

154
00:09:09,833 --> 00:09:12,100
- Dad! Dad!
- Greg!

155
00:09:12,233 --> 00:09:13,233
I'm here and Edward is here too.

156
00:09:13,367 --> 00:09:14,800
- Edward! Edward, come here!
- Edward!

157
00:09:14,933 --> 00:09:16,267
- Help me!
- He's still alive?

158
00:09:16,400 --> 00:09:18,933
He's still breathing! We need
to take him to the hospital now!

159
00:09:19,067 --> 00:09:21,600
- Dad!
- Hurry!

160
00:09:21,733 --> 00:09:23,800
- Hurry, take him!
- Dad!

161
00:09:23,933 --> 00:09:26,667
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

162
00:09:27,600 --> 00:09:29,700
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

163
00:09:30,433 --> 00:09:31,867
Greg, you'll be okay, okay?

164
00:09:32,733 --> 00:09:33,767
We're right here.

165
00:09:37,733 --> 00:09:39,067
- Greg.
- Ma'am, please stay here.

166
00:09:39,200 --> 00:09:40,433
We're sorry.

167
00:09:40,567 --> 00:09:42,733
We'll take care of him, okay?

168
00:09:44,800 --> 00:09:46,833
- Everything's going to be okay.
- Okay.

169
00:09:46,967 --> 00:09:48,333
Do you see now?

170
00:09:48,467 --> 00:09:49,667
Is this what you wanted?

171
00:09:49,800 --> 00:09:51,533
If you had just left our lives,

172
00:09:51,667 --> 00:09:52,900
this wouldn't have happened.

173
00:09:53,033 --> 00:09:55,200
Thea, can you please stop?

174
00:09:55,333 --> 00:09:57,433
Everyone's already worried,
and you still want to add to it?

175
00:09:59,167 --> 00:10:01,033
Why do you want the family
to fall apart?

176
00:10:01,200 --> 00:10:02,833
Edward and Paolo are fine, okay?

177
00:10:02,967 --> 00:10:03,867
You're the one who won't stop.

178
00:10:04,000 --> 00:10:05,633
Shut up!

179
00:10:05,767 --> 00:10:07,267
Now that the truth is out,

180
00:10:07,400 --> 00:10:10,300
you no longer have the right
to force yourselves in.

181
00:10:10,433 --> 00:10:13,033
Only the Torrecampos
have a say here,

182
00:10:13,167 --> 00:10:14,467
and you're not included.

183
00:10:14,600 --> 00:10:16,300
All of you, be quiet!

184
00:10:17,533 --> 00:10:19,433
Your father is fighting
for his life

185
00:10:19,567 --> 00:10:22,467
and you're here standing,
tearing each other apart.

186
00:10:22,600 --> 00:10:24,467
Whatever Greg's
shortcomings were,

187
00:10:24,600 --> 00:10:26,067
he is still the head
of this family

188
00:10:26,200 --> 00:10:28,200
and I suggest
that you remember that.

189
00:10:28,333 --> 00:10:30,900
Now, if you have any issues,
set them aside!

190
00:10:33,933 --> 00:10:35,967
<i>I heard what happened
to Greg Torrecampo.</i>

191
00:10:37,867 --> 00:10:40,933
Please, just send him flowers
and a fruit basket to his room.

192
00:10:41,667 --> 00:10:42,667
Thank you.

193
00:10:42,800 --> 00:10:45,500
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

194
00:10:50,933 --> 00:10:52,200
Did you hear that, Dad?

195
00:10:56,933 --> 00:10:59,700
They say the spouse of your
mistress had a heart attack.

196
00:11:01,133 --> 00:11:04,200
[WHIMPERING]

197
00:11:05,533 --> 00:11:06,733
Yes, Dad.

198
00:11:08,433 --> 00:11:09,667
Regina.

199
00:11:11,433 --> 00:11:15,033
The Torrecampos are slowly
self destructing.

200
00:11:16,300 --> 00:11:18,500
It's good you brought him
to the hospital right away.

201
00:11:18,633 --> 00:11:20,067
If you were 10 minutes late,

202
00:11:20,200 --> 00:11:22,300
we wouldn't be having
this conversation.

203
00:11:24,600 --> 00:11:25,767
How bad is it, Doc?

204
00:11:25,900 --> 00:11:27,733
He had a serious heart attack.

205
00:11:27,867 --> 00:11:31,433
For now, he needs absolute rest
and he must not be stressed.

206
00:11:31,667 --> 00:11:34,800
He needs to be careful because
the next one could be fatal.

207
00:11:37,667 --> 00:11:39,467
If you'll excuse me.

208
00:11:39,767 --> 00:11:40,933
Thank you, Doctor.

209
00:11:42,833 --> 00:11:43,967
Does it hurt?

210
00:11:46,367 --> 00:11:47,500
Does it hurt?

211
00:11:47,633 --> 00:11:51,333
- [WHIMPERING]
- Does it hurt?

212
00:11:52,767 --> 00:11:54,167
Is that enough?

213
00:11:56,100 --> 00:11:57,300
Enough?

214
00:11:59,867 --> 00:12:01,400
Why?

215
00:12:01,533 --> 00:12:02,700
- [WHIMPERING]
- Why?

216
00:12:03,733 --> 00:12:06,500
Did you stop back then even
when mom was already hurting?

217
00:12:10,433 --> 00:12:12,600
You're lucky to be alive.

218
00:12:13,300 --> 00:12:18,067
Maybe God gave you a second life
to correct your mistakes.

219
00:12:19,300 --> 00:12:22,533
So, you can make it up
to the people you hurt.

220
00:12:22,667 --> 00:12:26,800
So, please don't waste
this opportunity...

221
00:12:27,933 --> 00:12:30,733
because this might be
your last chance, Greg.

222
00:12:32,833 --> 00:12:35,567
<i>I'm not done getting revenge
on your mistress.</i>

223
00:12:36,900 --> 00:12:39,700
I still have many things
planned for her, Dad!

224
00:12:44,267 --> 00:12:45,800
I'm just getting started.

225
00:12:45,933 --> 00:12:50,067
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

226
00:12:51,700 --> 00:12:54,700
[WHIMPERING]

227
00:13:05,167 --> 00:13:09,200
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

228
00:13:09,333 --> 00:13:10,867
Where's everyone?

229
00:13:13,600 --> 00:13:17,533
They went home first to rest
and to check on the kids.

230
00:13:18,067 --> 00:13:21,700
Thank you for staying.

231
00:13:24,333 --> 00:13:25,467
You know...

232
00:13:27,167 --> 00:13:29,667
when I saw you having
a heart attack earlier...

233
00:13:31,233 --> 00:13:34,000
honestly, I didn't know
what to feel.

234
00:13:34,133 --> 00:13:37,067
Part of me wanted to leave you.

235
00:13:37,400 --> 00:13:40,067
I thought it was your karma.

236
00:13:40,467 --> 00:13:42,933
That this might also be the way
for all the suffering you caused

237
00:13:43,067 --> 00:13:44,067
to end.

238
00:13:46,033 --> 00:13:49,333
But here I am now, by your side.

239
00:13:51,167 --> 00:13:53,367
Watching over you.

240
00:13:53,667 --> 00:13:55,200
Waiting for you to be okay.

241
00:13:56,200 --> 00:13:59,733
Because no matter
how angry I am at you,

242
00:13:59,867 --> 00:14:02,633
even if I want to curse you,

243
00:14:02,867 --> 00:14:04,067
you're still my father.

244
00:14:06,400 --> 00:14:08,833
Even if my whole life you never
treated me as your child.

245
00:14:11,867 --> 00:14:14,167
Yet I can't forget
that you are my father.

246
00:14:18,367 --> 00:14:19,600
I'll...

247
00:14:19,733 --> 00:14:22,500
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

248
00:14:25,467 --> 00:14:27,200
I'll get stronger.

249
00:14:28,567 --> 00:14:29,867
I promise.

250
00:14:32,000 --> 00:14:37,967
I'll make it up to you
for all my shortcomings.

251
00:14:39,467 --> 00:14:43,400
[DRAMATIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

252
00:14:57,233 --> 00:14:59,267
Weng, after you change
the curtains,

253
00:14:59,400 --> 00:15:02,267
you can take the chair out
so there's more space here.

254
00:15:02,433 --> 00:15:06,867
The doctor said that dad
could be back any day by now.

255
00:15:07,000 --> 00:15:09,133
- Yes, Ma'am.
- Yes, Ma'am.

256
00:15:09,267 --> 00:15:13,500
Hey, after that,
fix our room as well.

257
00:15:13,633 --> 00:15:18,133
Because the real Torrecampos
will be living here again.

258
00:15:18,267 --> 00:15:20,733
So make sure everything
is perfect, okay?

259
00:15:21,900 --> 00:15:24,300
Thea, instead of being
concerned about dad,

260
00:15:24,433 --> 00:15:27,567
you're even more excited
about coming back here.

261
00:15:27,700 --> 00:15:28,867
What do you want?

262
00:15:29,000 --> 00:15:31,333
Should I show off like you?

263
00:15:31,467 --> 00:15:35,000
Marj, I'm sorry,
but I'm not fake

264
00:15:35,167 --> 00:15:39,900
or someone who sucks up
just to look good to dad.

265
00:15:40,033 --> 00:15:42,500
I'm not being fake, Thea.

266
00:15:42,633 --> 00:15:47,167
I care about dad
because he's my spouse's father.

267
00:15:47,300 --> 00:15:49,100
Correction.

268
00:15:49,233 --> 00:15:53,933
Father on paper only,
but they're not blood related.

269
00:15:54,067 --> 00:15:58,200
Edward is the only real child
of dad.

270
00:15:58,333 --> 00:16:02,333
So, you know, that showing off
and sucking up of yours,

271
00:16:02,467 --> 00:16:03,467
stop it already.

272
00:16:03,600 --> 00:16:05,267
Because no matter what you do,

273
00:16:05,400 --> 00:16:08,400
your reign as queen
in this house is over.

274
00:16:09,467 --> 00:16:11,067
It's my time now.

275
00:16:12,600 --> 00:16:14,800
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

276
00:16:18,267 --> 00:16:19,300
Careful, Sir.

277
00:16:20,500 --> 00:16:21,800
Thank you.

278
00:16:22,433 --> 00:16:23,700
Take it slowly.

279
00:16:28,633 --> 00:16:31,067
Dad, welcome back home.

280
00:16:31,200 --> 00:16:33,133
We're glad you're okay.

281
00:16:33,267 --> 00:16:34,700
Where is Ashley?

282
00:16:34,833 --> 00:16:36,900
She's with Jasmine.

283
00:16:37,033 --> 00:16:38,233
They're really excited.

284
00:16:38,367 --> 00:16:40,033
It's been a long time
since they saw each other.

285
00:16:40,167 --> 00:16:42,167
Edward, by the way, thank you
for watching over dad

286
00:16:42,333 --> 00:16:43,833
at the hospital.

287
00:16:43,967 --> 00:16:46,167
And welcome back home too.

288
00:16:48,400 --> 00:16:49,500
I don't want to live
in anger anymore.

289
00:16:50,700 --> 00:16:53,100
Let's just focus
on his recovery.

290
00:16:54,767 --> 00:16:56,600
- Cheche, Weng?
- Ma'am?

291
00:16:56,733 --> 00:17:00,500
Have you already fixed
the big room where we'll sleep?

292
00:17:00,633 --> 00:17:05,600
Actually, I told Cheche
that if possible,

293
00:17:05,733 --> 00:17:07,433
we'll stay in our old room
for now.

294
00:17:07,567 --> 00:17:10,233
What? That's small.

295
00:17:11,633 --> 00:17:14,233
I don't want dad to think
I feel entitled

296
00:17:14,400 --> 00:17:18,100
just because it was proven
I'm the real child.

297
00:17:20,367 --> 00:17:23,333
Dad, do you need anything?

298
00:17:23,467 --> 00:17:27,133
Would you like some hot tea
or anything else?

299
00:17:27,267 --> 00:17:28,467
No, thank you.

300
00:17:34,533 --> 00:17:35,767
Is there a problem?

301
00:17:39,433 --> 00:17:40,133
No.

302
00:17:40,933 --> 00:17:46,367
I'm just not used to seeing you
so caring and attentive.

303
00:17:47,300 --> 00:17:49,500
So, what's your point?

304
00:17:49,667 --> 00:17:51,900
That I'm not sincere?

305
00:17:52,033 --> 00:17:55,267
You know, Marj, not everything
I do has ulterior motives.

306
00:17:56,767 --> 00:18:00,333
I've also woken up to the truth
that we're family.

307
00:18:00,467 --> 00:18:03,367
And family helps each other.

308
00:18:03,500 --> 00:18:05,300
Especially at times like this.

309
00:18:06,767 --> 00:18:07,900
Right, Dad?

310
00:18:09,233 --> 00:18:11,833
Jas, why do we still need
to leave the house?

311
00:18:11,967 --> 00:18:13,433
We could just chill there,
right?

312
00:18:14,733 --> 00:18:16,133
Because even if we stay at home,

313
00:18:16,267 --> 00:18:18,900
it feels like you really
can't breathe.

314
00:18:19,033 --> 00:18:21,500
It's like everyone is on edge.

315
00:18:21,667 --> 00:18:23,567
Yes, it feels heavy, right?

316
00:18:26,533 --> 00:18:30,867
So, I thought maybe you deserve
a little time off

317
00:18:31,000 --> 00:18:32,267
even just briefly.

318
00:18:32,400 --> 00:18:34,233
Like what you used to do for me.

319
00:18:35,133 --> 00:18:36,233
What?

320
00:18:37,233 --> 00:18:38,467
When I was sick,

321
00:18:38,967 --> 00:18:41,067
you distracted me.

322
00:18:41,200 --> 00:18:44,300
You always made me laugh,
took me out.

323
00:18:44,433 --> 00:18:46,333
So now, it's my turn.

324
00:18:46,467 --> 00:18:47,533
What's this?

325
00:18:47,667 --> 00:18:48,800
Close your eyes.

326
00:18:48,933 --> 00:18:51,733
- Why?
- Just close your eyes.

327
00:18:56,667 --> 00:19:00,600
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

328
00:19:00,733 --> 00:19:02,033
Open.

329
00:19:06,633 --> 00:19:07,733
Surprise!

330
00:19:10,633 --> 00:19:11,567
Xander?

331
00:19:11,867 --> 00:19:14,167
Okay, I'll leave you two.

332
00:19:14,400 --> 00:19:16,733
Ash, for once, just enjoy it.

333
00:19:19,433 --> 00:19:20,667
Thank you, cousin.

334
00:19:21,367 --> 00:19:22,567
Thank you, guys.

335
00:19:23,400 --> 00:19:24,700
Enjoy!

336
00:19:24,833 --> 00:19:28,500
[MELLOW MUSIC PLAYING]

337
00:19:31,567 --> 00:19:34,333
I believe Edward that despite
everything that happened,

338
00:19:34,467 --> 00:19:36,633
he wants to fix the family.

339
00:19:36,767 --> 00:19:39,233
But Thea, I'm not convinced.

340
00:19:39,367 --> 00:19:42,867
She's getting close to dad
and clearly trying to look good.

341
00:19:43,200 --> 00:19:45,000
I know she'll find a way

342
00:19:45,133 --> 00:19:48,433
to push us out of the house
and the Torrecampos' lives.

343
00:19:49,767 --> 00:19:53,267
Thea has always known
how to position herself.

344
00:19:53,400 --> 00:19:55,933
She won't move
without something to gain.

345
00:19:56,967 --> 00:19:59,267
So please, Marj, I'm asking you.

346
00:19:59,400 --> 00:20:04,133
Watch Thea closely.
Don't let her cause trouble.

347
00:20:04,300 --> 00:20:05,933
You can count on me, Mom.

348
00:20:06,067 --> 00:20:08,867
I won't let her manipulate dad.

349
00:20:10,033 --> 00:20:11,133
Thank you, Marj.

350
00:20:11,267 --> 00:20:15,267
Don't let Thea destroy the
family we're trying to rebuild.

351
00:20:15,400 --> 00:20:18,567
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

352
00:20:21,533 --> 00:20:23,000
Careful, Dad.

353
00:20:23,133 --> 00:20:24,833
Take small bites.

354
00:20:24,967 --> 00:20:26,200
There.

355
00:20:33,800 --> 00:20:37,567
Dad, haven't you thought
about it?

356
00:20:37,733 --> 00:20:40,133
What happened to you
could happen again.

357
00:20:41,233 --> 00:20:44,633
I mean, we have to be realistic.

358
00:20:46,300 --> 00:20:50,067
We don't know
when our time will come.

359
00:20:50,200 --> 00:20:53,900
But we can prepare
what we leave behind.

360
00:20:57,233 --> 00:20:59,500
Especially Edward.

361
00:20:59,633 --> 00:21:01,200
His whole life,

362
00:21:01,333 --> 00:21:03,867
he never experienced
the life he deserved.

363
00:21:05,600 --> 00:21:07,533
Only now has he had a chance.

364
00:21:10,500 --> 00:21:12,533
So maybe, Dad,

365
00:21:12,667 --> 00:21:14,933
while you're still strong,

366
00:21:15,067 --> 00:21:17,267
you should also fix
your last will.

367
00:21:20,967 --> 00:21:23,500
Just to be sure

368
00:21:23,633 --> 00:21:26,533
that he won't be left behind
or disadvantaged again.

369
00:21:27,633 --> 00:21:28,600
Thea.

370
00:21:28,733 --> 00:21:30,333
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

371
00:21:33,633 --> 00:21:37,100
Stop pressuring dad
about those matters.

372
00:21:37,333 --> 00:21:38,633
He just got out of the hospital

373
00:21:38,900 --> 00:21:40,300
and money is already
your concern?

374
00:21:41,067 --> 00:21:42,500
Excuse me, Marj.

375
00:21:42,667 --> 00:21:45,433
I'm just being practical
and realistic here.

376
00:21:45,567 --> 00:21:48,667
I'm just making sure
what's secured for my spouse.

377
00:21:48,800 --> 00:21:51,600
Why? Is it wrong to think about
the family's future?

378
00:21:52,233 --> 00:21:54,133
Dad is still recovering.

379
00:21:54,500 --> 00:21:56,700
Yet you're reminding him
about death?

380
00:22:00,667 --> 00:22:02,400
Dad, are you okay?

381
00:22:04,267 --> 00:22:08,000
Do you want to go inside
so you can rest properly?

382
00:22:08,333 --> 00:22:10,200
You don't need stress right now.

383
00:22:10,967 --> 00:22:11,700
Okay, Dad.

384
00:22:16,667 --> 00:22:19,667
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

385
00:22:29,133 --> 00:22:30,567
This is so irritating!

386
00:22:30,700 --> 00:22:32,133
Seriously!

387
00:22:32,500 --> 00:22:34,800
That Marj is just too much
of a show off as always.

388
00:22:34,933 --> 00:22:37,033
There's nothing wrong
with what I suggested to dad.

389
00:22:38,100 --> 00:22:39,533
Marj does have a point.

390
00:22:40,600 --> 00:22:42,667
Is money and inheritance
really all you're after?

391
00:22:44,433 --> 00:22:46,067
Hey, Edward.

392
00:22:46,200 --> 00:22:48,767
Our future is at stake here.

393
00:22:48,933 --> 00:22:51,300
So, let's seize
this opportunity.

394
00:22:52,133 --> 00:22:54,067
You know,
just a little push more,

395
00:22:54,200 --> 00:22:57,867
you'll get back everything
you deserve in this house.

396
00:22:58,000 --> 00:22:59,500
Even the company of your family.

397
00:22:59,633 --> 00:23:01,367
I didn't come back here
for money.

398
00:23:03,167 --> 00:23:04,700
I'm here because I want...

399
00:23:04,967 --> 00:23:06,567
I want to reconcile with dad.

400
00:23:07,900 --> 00:23:09,733
I want to feel
that I have a father.

401
00:23:10,367 --> 00:23:11,800
Before he's gone.

402
00:23:13,000 --> 00:23:14,633
I want to fix this family.

403
00:23:14,767 --> 00:23:16,767
Not to scavenge for inheritance.

404
00:23:16,900 --> 00:23:18,667
Edward, come on!

405
00:23:19,133 --> 00:23:20,733
Ashley and I are your family.

406
00:23:20,867 --> 00:23:22,500
We should be your priority.

407
00:23:22,667 --> 00:23:24,667
Ashley will have a good future.

408
00:23:24,800 --> 00:23:27,767
And I'll make sure of that
without competing with Paolo

409
00:23:27,900 --> 00:23:29,467
over the inheritance.

410
00:23:29,600 --> 00:23:33,300
If I need to work twice as hard
for my child, I'll do it.

411
00:23:34,333 --> 00:23:37,000
But don't expect me
to use dad's illness

412
00:23:37,133 --> 00:23:38,800
to squeeze out money.

413
00:23:38,933 --> 00:23:42,233
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

414
00:23:48,600 --> 00:23:50,433
If you won't act,

415
00:23:50,567 --> 00:23:53,767
then I'll find a way myself.

416
00:23:53,900 --> 00:23:56,533
[INTENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

417
00:23:59,100 --> 00:24:02,633
Dad, the doctor said it would be
good for you to exercise.

418
00:24:02,767 --> 00:24:04,167
Let's do this every day.

419
00:24:08,533 --> 00:24:11,600
Marj, thank you.

420
00:24:11,733 --> 00:24:13,533
Not just for this.

421
00:24:14,633 --> 00:24:20,700
But for taking care of me
even when I didn't deserve it.

422
00:24:21,933 --> 00:24:27,867
I know how serious
my sins against you were.

423
00:24:28,000 --> 00:24:30,133
Dad, please don't think about
that anymore.

424
00:24:30,400 --> 00:24:32,867
What matters is
that you get stronger.

425
00:24:33,000 --> 00:24:33,867
No.

426
00:24:34,900 --> 00:24:36,633
I have to say this.

427
00:24:38,400 --> 00:24:40,367
Please forgive me...

428
00:24:42,500 --> 00:24:44,367
if I hid...

429
00:24:45,400 --> 00:24:48,333
the affair of Paolo and Thea.

430
00:24:49,467 --> 00:24:54,867
If I consent to keeping it
a secret

431
00:24:55,833 --> 00:24:58,533
that Ashley is Paolo's child.

432
00:24:59,500 --> 00:25:04,267
And also what I did
to your mother.

433
00:25:06,767 --> 00:25:08,967
I regret all of that now.

434
00:25:11,300 --> 00:25:18,600
I hope it's not too late for me
to make it up to you.

435
00:25:18,733 --> 00:25:22,833
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

436
00:25:26,533 --> 00:25:31,500
I also want to thank you
for all your efforts.

437
00:25:33,767 --> 00:25:38,300
You're the one who keep us
together.

438
00:25:39,600 --> 00:25:41,067
Thank you, Marj.

439
00:25:44,133 --> 00:25:45,400
Thank you, Dad.

440
00:25:46,367 --> 00:25:47,767
Thank you.

441
00:25:47,900 --> 00:25:52,367
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

442
00:25:55,633 --> 00:25:57,867
You really are a spoiler
as always, Marj.

443
00:25:59,367 --> 00:26:02,467
I will never let you
become the favorites

444
00:26:02,600 --> 00:26:05,033
and outdo us again.

445
00:26:05,167 --> 00:26:08,400
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

446
00:26:10,700 --> 00:26:13,300
Marj, I know I don't deserve
a second chance.

447
00:26:13,433 --> 00:26:15,000
But I'll still fight for it.

448
00:26:15,133 --> 00:26:19,533
So even if I have to court you
every day, I'll do it.

449
00:26:19,667 --> 00:26:20,900
What are you talking about?

450
00:26:21,033 --> 00:26:22,233
You know if I hadn't arrived,

451
00:26:22,367 --> 00:26:24,133
dad might have fallen
and drowned.

452
00:26:24,267 --> 00:26:25,567
And it's all your fault!

453
00:26:25,700 --> 00:26:27,467
You know you should be
the one watching him.

454
00:26:27,600 --> 00:26:28,567
That's not true.

455
00:26:28,700 --> 00:26:29,700
I saw something else!

456
00:26:29,833 --> 00:26:31,133
You're so shameless!

457
00:26:31,267 --> 00:26:32,600
You're really accusing me?

458
00:26:32,733 --> 00:26:34,033
Your mind is filthy!

459
00:26:34,167 --> 00:26:36,200
Why don't you
rinse yourself off first?

460
00:26:36,333 --> 00:26:37,633
[SQUEALS]

461
00:26:37,767 --> 00:26:39,267
[WATER SPLASHING]

462
00:26:39,400 --> 00:26:40,833
Stop it!

463
00:26:40,967 --> 00:26:42,433
Marj!

464
00:26:43,767 --> 00:26:45,033
Thea, stop it!

465
00:26:46,200 --> 00:26:47,867
I lost control.

466
00:26:48,000 --> 00:26:49,400
That's it?
And you almost killed Marj

467
00:26:49,533 --> 00:26:51,000
over something that shallow?

468
00:26:51,133 --> 00:26:54,100
I'm tired of dealing with
someone who will do anything

469
00:26:54,233 --> 00:26:57,233
even evil just for ambition!

470
00:26:57,367 --> 00:26:58,367
I give up.

471
00:26:58,500 --> 00:27:01,467
I'm done playing games with you.

472
00:27:01,600 --> 00:27:03,633
What are you saying?
[STAMMERS]

473
00:27:03,767 --> 00:27:04,933
Let's end this.

474
00:27:05,067 --> 00:27:06,433
Let's separate.

475
00:27:08,000 --> 00:27:11,667
Thea, get out of my house!

476
00:27:11,800 --> 00:27:13,700
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]
